heaviest_rainfall.status: The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 04 January 2025, with precipitation totalling 36.8mm.  The rain fell at 4.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 10th ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 10.1mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  9.37mm of rain fell during the storm's 16.6 hours length.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.0mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 10th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 16.6 hours.  9.37mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 10.1mm per hour.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.
